{"TopicId":182108,"ForumId":18,"TopicTitle":"Toilet training a cat.","CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-12T00:19:47Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-12T00:19:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have to wonder, has anyone here toilet trained a cat, or has a cat that was toilet trained? I\u0027m in the process of toilet training our cat, using the book\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.amazon.ca/Toilet-Train-Your-Cat-Accident-Free-ebook/dp/B00PSNRQIS\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E Toilet Training Your Cat: Relaxed Cats DIY Accident Free Guide\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0by Marian Pack. I was able to download a free copy for the Kobo eReader app on my iPhone.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m currently at what I\u0027m calling Step 2: Building a mock toilet: Step 0 was moving the litter box to the bathroom, and step 1 was elevating it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022UVlgwjW.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022768\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/UVlgwjW.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022576\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0He\u0027s using it, so I think this might actually work. Has anyone else tried this?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know patience and a stress-free cat is the trick. I wanted to try this much sooner, but we had gotten a puppy, and then when I was ready to try it he came down with a urinary issue (crystal formations needing a special (read:expensive) food). Now that I have a happy cat again, it was time to try.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Chel","CreatedById":176173,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-12T00:23:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI attempted to train mine, and it kinda worked. Instead of either peeing on the floor or in the litter box, she actually jumps up on the sink and pees in there.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-12T00:25:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223539020\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182108\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549931026\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176173\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The_Cat_In_Space\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, The_Cat_In_Space said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI attempted to train mine, and it kinda worked. Instead of either peeing on the floor or in the litter box, she actually jumps up on the sink and pees in there.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHmmm, a common accident according to that book, especially if the cat gets confused...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Chel","CreatedById":176173,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-12T00:26:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223539022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182108\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549931119\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289439\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StrandedonEarth\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, StrandedonEarth said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHmmm, a common accident according to that book, especially if the cat gets confused...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut it solved the problem of having to clean up cat pee, so I\u0027m happy\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-12T00:29:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223539025\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182108\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549931196\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176173\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The_Cat_In_Space\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, The_Cat_In_Space said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut it solved the problem of having to clean up cat pee, so I\u0027m happy\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFair enough, but where does he poop, still in the litter box? Any particular method or guide you followed?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFigures this thread would\u00A0get a reply from a space cat...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-02-12T00:30:05Z\u0022 title=\u002202/12/2019 12:30  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 12, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by StrandedonEarth\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Chel","CreatedById":176173,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-12T00:33:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223539027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182108\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549931354\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289439\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StrandedonEarth\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, StrandedonEarth said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFair enough, but where does he poop, still in the litter box? Any particular method or guide you followed?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFigures this thread would\u00A0get a reply from a space cat...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nShe poops outside or in the litter box, and I didn\u0027t really follow a guide.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe second I saw \u0027cat\u0027 in the title I was interested \u003Cspan\u003E:3\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-12T01:20:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYears a go a college housemate tried this with his cats. I think it worked with one, while the other stood on the seat and crapped on the floor.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey didn\u0027t like being watched, so he never figured which was which.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-12T01:47:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223539057\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182108\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549934454\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tater\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n26 minutes ago, tater said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhile the other stood on the seat and crapped on the floor.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, his first crap landed on the mock toilet seat, and he scooped a lot of litter on the floor trying to bury it, but at least he\u0027s trying to use it. It\u0027s a learning experience for both of us....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-02-12T01:47:55Z\u0022 title=\u002202/12/2019 01:47  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 12, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by StrandedonEarth\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-12T01:55:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGood luck!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-12T05:28:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223539016\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182108\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549930787\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289439\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StrandedonEarth\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, StrandedonEarth said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0He\u0027s using it, so I think this might actually work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow don\u0027t take them confused yourself when sleepy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223539016\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182108\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549930787\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289439\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StrandedonEarth\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, StrandedonEarth said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\na stress-free cat\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA cat doesn\u0027t have a stress. Humans do.\u003Cbr\u003E\nOnly stressed humans produce a cat\u0027s stress. Just take it easy and don\u0027t stress him, and you will have a stress-free cat.\u003Cbr\u003E\n(\u003Cem\u003EHim\u003C/em\u003E because \u003Cem\u003Eher\u0027s\u003C/em\u003E usually don\u0027t put marks everywhere.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223539022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182108\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549931119\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289439\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StrandedonEarth\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, StrandedonEarth said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223539020\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182108\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549931026\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176173\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The_Cat_In_Space\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, The_Cat_In_Space said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI attempted to train mine, and it kinda worked. Instead of either peeing on the floor or in the litter box, she actually jumps up on the sink and pees in there.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHmmm, a common accident according to that book, especially if the cat gets confused..\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNay, the cat gets relaxed. Humans do.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223539031\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182108\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549931589\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176173\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The_Cat_In_Space\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, The_Cat_In_Space said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nShe poops outside\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBorn to be wild...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223539057\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182108\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549934454\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tater\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, tater said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthe other stood on the seat and crapped on the floor.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA gravity cat. It deserves a personal meme.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nP.S.\u003Cbr\u003E\nThe furry jerks hate the smell of kerosene. As well, the kerosene hides the smell of their marks.\u003Cbr\u003E\nSo, we were using it as 2-in-1: to wash the cat\u00A0marks and to make the cats avoid the most attractive places and resentfully hide in a toilet.\u003Cbr\u003E\n(Probably they thought: \u0022What a smelly jerk is a human. A cat even can\u0027t 3.14 where\u00A0they have put the human marks.\u0022)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-12T11:40:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223539202\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182108\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549949299\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA cat doesn\u0027t have a stress.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA sick or injured cat, or a cat dealing with a lot of change, is a stressed cat. \u0022What the heck is this big dumb puppy doing in\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Emy space?!?\u0022\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-12T11:42:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223539330\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182108\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549971624\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289439\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StrandedonEarth\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, StrandedonEarth said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA sick or injured cat, or a cat dealing with a lot of change, is a stressed ca\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003Et.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI mean, the cat having toilet where he/she wants.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-02-12T11:46:13Z\u0022 title=\u002202/12/2019 11:46  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 12, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"benzman","CreatedById":82512,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-12T19:55:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKittens are toilet trained by their mothers.\u00A0 If you have a cat that doesn\u0027t go outside or use its litter tray it was probably taken from its mother too early.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-12T21:38:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223539567\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182108\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221550001354\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002282512\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022benzman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, benzman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKittens are toilet trained by their mothers.\u00A0 If you have a cat that doesn\u0027t go outside or use its litter tray it was probably taken from its mother too early.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh, the cat is litter trained. I want it toilet trained so no more buying and scooping litter\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"benzman","CreatedById":82512,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-13T05:40:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223539626\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182108\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221550007500\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289439\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StrandedonEarth\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, StrandedonEarth said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh, the cat is litter trained. I want it toilet trained so no more buying and scooping litter\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGood luck with that!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nightside","CreatedById":150244,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-09T14:56:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy cat Truffle would poop but not pee in it\u00A0so I\u00A0gave up on it.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u2019s quite annoying when you only have 1 toilet. I like your idea of training on a box.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LordFerret","CreatedById":111598,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-09T16:36:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWait until it starts complaining you\u0027ve left the lid up.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-09T17:39:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223555008\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182108\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221552149390\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111598\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022LordFerret\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, LordFerret said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWait until it starts complaining you\u0027ve left the lid up.\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe cat is training to do it himself.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022dsu00016.gif\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022147\u0022 src=\u0022http://dereza.su/images/stories/GIF/dsu00016.gif\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Green Baron","CreatedById":107381,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-09T17:40:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223539626\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182108\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221550007500\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289439\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StrandedonEarth\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/12/2019 at 9:38 PM, StrandedonEarth said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh, the cat is litter trained. I want it toilet trained so no more buying and scooping litter\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t do that. It could slip and drown, but it probably won\u0027t step on the bowl for fear of that to happen.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI grew up with cats and we always had boxes with cat litter. Change it once there something in it because some cats won\u0027t use it twice.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd a few years ago i adopted a stray cat, that one actually goes out for business (enough space in the \u0022garden\u0022).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCompared to other animals, the usual household cat is so unproblematic, a few minutes petting each day, food and changing litter and cleaning up the remains of small rodents or lizards is all there is to do. Only some overbred races may need more care.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-09T18:13:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCats usually have to go and mark stuff too. So you might have to take that into consideration.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere most people who \u0027own\u0027 cats are usually just letting it out and in. It\u0027ll come back at night then go out in the day. They just come for food and shelter,\u00A0not much else. They\u0027ll do the other stuff themselves - you don\u0027t need to give more. While I don\u0027t own a cat, I know of cats which frequent my house, and who will just sleep in front of the house all day long. We even had a feral cat giving birth at my home once, so it was de facto their home for a few months. The car is usually a good place for the cats - esp. after usage, since they\u0027re warm. Furnitures and mats too, they feel warmer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LordFerret","CreatedById":111598,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-09T23:17:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223555071\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182108\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221552155237\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002298447\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022YNM\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, YNM said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCat\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003Es usually have\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E to go and mark st\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003Euff to\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003Eo\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s a lot I could say about that ... dogs and ferrets do also ... but for cats, \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.humanesociety.org/resources/cat-marking-territory\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Eread this\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-10T01:13:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223555261\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182108\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221552173445\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111598\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022LordFerret\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, LordFerret said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbut\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E for cats, \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.humanesociety.org/resources/cat-marking-territory\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Eread \u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003Ethis\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, I\u0027m basing it off of feral cats where I live. They don\u0027t normally do it to your things (like, only a few\u00A0times in a few years), but one of the listed reasons there\u00A0was \u0022mating behaviour\u0022, which feral cats engages in. I\u0027ve never really notice it for cats which are exclusively confined in a house, because I rarely see one - most people just leave the cat to be and they\u0027ll go out when they need to.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-10T07:23:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223555261\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182108\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221552173445\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111598\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022LordFerret\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, LordFerret said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbut for cats, \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.humanesociety.org/resources/cat-marking-territory\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Eread this\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nQuote\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:rgb(41,57,65);\u0022\u003EThere are several possible reasons your cat is urine marking:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey missed the main reason: from pure evil. Because the cat hates that you hate his cutie marks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-03-10T07:24:04Z\u0022 title=\u002203/10/2019 07:24  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 10, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klesh","CreatedById":110814,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-11T15:55:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat kind of a cat?\u00A0 Some are smarter than others.\u00A0 I have a silver bengal that I have no doubt would be able to learn this.\u00A0 I\u0027m cool with him using a litter box, so I\u0027ve never attempted to train him to use the toilet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-11T18:26:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223556593\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182108\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221552319725\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110814\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022klesh\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, klesh said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat kind of a cat?\u00A0 Some are smarter than others.\u00A0 I have a silver bengal that I have no doubt would be able to learn this.\u00A0 I\u0027m cool with him using a litter box, so I\u0027ve never attempted to train him to use the toilet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u2019ve been meaning to update this thread. I believe it\u2019s an orange tabby cat (kinda peachy coloured). Small head so maybe not as bright as some, but doesn\u2019t\u00A0seem too dumb. As for concerns about slipping off, a padded seat is recommended for grip, and it\u2019s not a trick for declawed cats to try!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHe\u2019s doing fine on his mock toilet so far. A week ago I tried the next step of burying a small container of water in the litter, but he avoided it for two days (got outside at one point so not like he was bursting). So I took that out, and will soon try again with a smaller, shot-glass-sizes container. But first I think I need to turn the seat around so he has to stand on the seat, with no room around it.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSlow and steady is the trick. An end to scooping litter is the reward, so no rush if I want to get there.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}